Many doctors assume that aspirin will also provide some benefit for people with vascular dementia.
This systematic review shows that there is no evidence to suggest that aspirin is useful for people with vascular dementia.
It is possible that vascular dementia and stroke are caused by different pathological processes.
Practitioners need to be aware of the risks of aspirin, such as haemorrhages, which can be fatal.